      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:65:8",
      "text": [
        " لَا بَأْسَ بِأَنْ يَكُونَ التَّمَاثِيلُ فِي الْبُيُوتِ إِذَا غُيِّرَتْ رُءُوسُهَا مِنْهَا وَ تُرِكَ مَا سِوَى ذَلِكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Jameel Bin Darraj, from Zurara Bin Ayn, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘There is no problem if there happen to be the resemblances in the houses when its heads are changed from it and it is left, what is besides that’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "8. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Jamil ibn Darraj from Zurarah ibn ’A‘yan who has said the following: “Abu Ja‘far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘The existence of al-Tamathil (pictures or statues) in a house is not harmful if their heads are changed and the rest is left.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
